\s+2License Agreement and Warranty\s-2

The HBUILD6 program, its documentation, and all other included
software are copyrighted with
all rights reserved.  The user is granted a license to use this software on
a single Model 4, 4D or 4P system. 

This product contains serial numbers and other traceable markings.
LS-DOS 6.3 systems utilize the serialized protection system to enforce
this agreement.

Companies or
individuals with multiple systems must obtain a multiple-system version.

The user may make one (1) backup of the diskette for archival purposes.

The manufacturer warrants the diskette media on which HBUILD6 is recorded
to be free from defects under normal use for a period of 90 days from the
date of original purchase.  If during this 90 day period a defect in the
diskette media makes the recorded data unusable, you may return the
diskette to the manufacturer for replacement without charge.  The
user does pay the cost of delivering the diskette to the manufacturer.

The manufacturer makes no commitment to provide any upgrade.  However, if
one is produced, the following upgrade policy will apply:

.in .5i
If an upgrade version of HBUILD6 (or a directly-related utility) becomes
available during the 90 day warranty period, the user will be advised to
return the original diskette to the manufacturer (provided the user has
registered within 10 days of purchase) for replacement without charge.

After 90 days, any upgrade software that is made available will be
provided at a nominal charge when the user returns the original, unaltered,
and usable diskette.

.in 0i
Any diskette that is returned due to a defect for an in-warranty exchange or
for an upgrade (in or out of warranty) that has a defaced or invalid
registration number, or has been modified or totally erased will not be
accepted.

The registration card must be mailed within 10 days of purchase or filled
out when the purchase is made.

Except as provided for above, the author and/or manufacturer make no
warranties, either expressed or implied, with respect to this software
or its fitness for any purpose.  This software is provided "as-is".  Although
significant testing has been performed to insure that this product will
work with the systems listed, this software cannot be expected to work
in systems other than those listed and on versions of operating systems
other than the ones specified.   Non-standard versions of 
hardware or software can also prevent this product from functioning
as intended.   Should the software prove defective or incompatible, the
user assumes the entire cost of all necessary servicing, repair, or
correction and any incidental or consequential damages.  The author and
manufacturer assume no liability for direct, indirect, incidental or
consequential damages resulting from any use of or any defects in the
software.




